Well, I can see a mess in that code, so I would suggest, instead of just helping to fix it... a different path, so you can have total control in what&#39;s going on and making it also easier to improve and fix any code:

Because you are repeating your code and using small chunks of HTML, I would strongly suggest a very small tool, like [JsRender](https://www.jsviews.com/#jsrender) from one of our [members](https://stackoverflow.com/users/1054484/borismoore) (you could use [Handlebars](https://handlebarsjs.com/) or [Mustache](https://github.com/janl/mustache.js) as well, but they are a bit bigger and with too much functionality we will not even use)

for such, I would then do:

- have an array with all your URL&#39;s
- go through them all
- to be easier to manipulate, append child data to parent object
- save all data into a global object
- render your template with the gathered data

a caveat:

if **you can use Promises**, you can take advantage of firing all 3 requests at once and wait until all are done and go from there... for example:

```javascript

  var settings = [
    // categories
    &#39;https://api.myjson.com/bins/nilct&#39;,
    // questions
    &#39;https://api.myjson.com/bins/1178p1&#39;,
    // answers
    &#39;https://api.myjson.com/bins/qhft1&#39;,
  ];


  Promise.all([
    getData(settings[0]),
    getData(settings[1]),
    getData(settings[2])
  ]).then(function(allData) {
    var categories = allData[0],
        questions = allData[1],
        answers = allData[2];
    
    // append all categoties to our global object
    formData = categories;
    // append all questions to each category
    formData.forEach(function(x) {
      x.questions = questions;
      // append all answers to each question
      x.questions.forEach(function(y) {
        y.answers = answers;
      });
    });

  processData(formData, &#39;#tmplForm&#39;, &#39;#main-quiz&#39;);
```

