answers.body_markdown:
There is multiple options.

I will suggest you to do as the following :

In your script that changes one of your material, call a function like
```csharp
public void ChangeMaterial(Material m, int index){
    GetComponent&lt;Renderer&gt;().materials[index] = m;
}
```

If you want to change your material multiple times, you&#39;d probably want to cache the `Renderer` component.

There is a full script example

```csharp
public class MyScript : MonoBehaviour
{
    private Renderer _renderer;

    private void Start(){
        _renderer = GetComponent&lt;Renderer&gt;();
    }

    public void ChangeMaterial(Material m, int index){
        _renderer.materials[index] = m;
    }
}
```

